title.narrative: Response for HIV and for STIs in Madagascar: an approach involving the populations most exposed in the zones of vulnerability

description.narrative: Madagascar - HIV - Sécrétariat Exécutif du Comité National de Lutte Contre le VIH/SIDA de la République de Madagascar - SE/CNLS. This program has the following goals: The proportion of HIV-infected infants born to HIV-positive mothers is reduced to less than 5% by the end of 2017.. The proportion of people living with HIV who are alive and on ART at 12 months after treatment initiation is increased to 95% by the end of 2017.. The number of new HIV infections is reduced by at least 50%, among key populations who are the most exposed to the risk of HIV infection and among the general population, by the end of 2017.. The objectives of this program are: At least 80% of the key populations most exposed to HIV, and 60% of people with unstable heterosexual partnerships, adopt behaviours and practices that reduce their risk by the end of 2017.. At least 80% of HIV-positive pregnant women receive a service package to reduce HIV transmission from mother to child by the end of 2017.. At least 60% of women of childbearing age adopt HIV prevention practices by the end of 2017.. The risk of HIV transmission through blood transfusion is reduced by at least 50% by the end of 2017.. At least 80% of adults and children living with HIV receive medical, psychosocial, social and legal services by the end of 2017.
